docs.lead_paragraph: Germany’s three largest carmakers secretly agreed to equip their vehicles with inferior emissions equipment, European authorities said Friday, a finding that could expose Volkswagen, Daimler and BMW to a large share of the blame for poor air quality in Europe that is believed to cause thousands of deaths annually.

docs.abstract: Outsiders have little leverage to force the industry to change. The companies’ own workers are another matter.

docs.lead_paragraph: For a few hours last Thursday, just about everything at Google ground to a halt. At 11 a.m. local time in a movement that rolled like an angry and jubilant tide around the globe, more than 20,000 employees walked out to protest the company’s long history of protecting executives accused of sexual harassment.

headline.main: Why the Google Walkout Was a Watershed Moment in Tech
